notes.note:
Customer emailed:
Hi there, 

Just want to understando how the claim system works, need to be a mechanic listed by your company or could be the mechanic that I trust?
Its time to change the timing chain on my car so just want to clarify how this works. 

Thank you in advance.
Thiago Vieira
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I replied:
Thanks for your email.
Repairs for covered components must be performed at a Canada General authorized repair facility.
You can log onto canadageneral.ca and click on "Contact Us". There you will find a map showing all of our authorized 
Repair facilities, highlighted with blue pointers.
That being said, preventative replacement of timing belts is not covered by the warranty nor is the timing chain unless there is breakage.
I trust this answers your questions.
If you have further questions, please feel free to contact us.

Sincerely,
Adam Halko
Claims Manager

notes.note: Customer bought the bike in May of 2023. Says within two weeks he had an issue with the hanger bearing, took it to Auto Nexus to have it addressed, they ordered a part and told him it was back ordered. Customer went to an after market part source for the hanger bearing on the drive shaft of his bike, installed the new one and was promised by Auto Nexus that they would reimburse him. Did not receive reimbursement. Roughly 1 month after this, bike was sitting idling in front of his garage and caught fire. Customer had to put bike out with fire extinguisher. Had this issue along with several other issues all during his 6 month manufacturers warranty period, but when he went to have the previously mentioned items and other items addressed, found that Auto Nexus went out of business and wanted to know how to proceed. Informed him that he needs to seek legal assistance for any of the damage or issues that occurred within the 6 month manufacturers warranty, as we cannot submit a claim for stuff that should have been covered under man. warranty. Customer says he did not receive any paper work or proof of work that was performed by Auto Nexus. Informed customer that he cannot submit a claim for any items that have malfunctioned as a result of the issues that occurred within 6 month period after purchase as they are a result of something that should have been covered by manufacturer's warranty. notes.content: Customer bought the bike in May of 2023. Says within two weeks he had an issue with the hanger bearing, took it to Auto Nexus to have it addressed, they ordered a part and told him it was back ordered. Customer went to an after market part source for the hanger bearing on the drive shaft of his bike, installed the new one and was promised by Auto Nexus that they would reimburse him. Did not receive reimbursement. Roughly 1 month after this, bike was sitting idling in front of his garage and caught fire. Customer had to put bike out with fire extinguisher. Had this issue along with several other issues all during his 6 month manufacturers warranty period, but when he went to have the previously mentioned items and other items addressed, found that Auto Nexus went out of business and wanted to know how to proceed. Informed him that he needs to seek legal assistance for any of the damage or issues that occurred within the 6 month manufacturers warranty, as we cannot submit a claim for stuff that should have been covered under man. warranty.
